      "id": "ml89h6fx",
      "questionNumber": 14,
      "subject": "Chemistry",
      "section": "A",
      "questionType": "MCQ",
      "questionText": "<p>Given below are two statements :</p>\n<p><b>Statement I :</b> Sucrose is dextrorotatory. However, sucrose upon hydrolysis gives a solution having mixture of products. This solution shows laevorotation.</p>\n<p><b>Statement II :</b> Hydrolysis of sucrose gives glucose and fructose. Since the laevorotation of glucose is more than the dextrorotation of fructose, the resulting solution becomes laevorotatory.</p>\n<p>In the light of the above statements, choose the correct answer from the options given below :</p>",
      "options": [
        "<p>Both Statement I and Statement II are false</p>\n",
        "<p>Both Statement I and Statement II are true</p>\n",
        "<p>Statement I is true but Statement II is false</p>\n",
        "<p>Statement I is false but Statement II is true</p>"
      ],
      "correctOption": 2,
      "solution": "<p><img alt=\"JEE Main 2026 (Online) 22nd January Morning Shift Chemistry - Biomolecules Question 15 English Explanation\" src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1mlg85w6d/2480ca88-070e-4144-a325-4e6ee5cb090e/69e15e40-064a-11f1-b922-e51ff66e4291/file-6y3zli1mlg85w6e.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1mlg85w6d/2480ca88-070e-4144-a325-4e6ee5cb090e/69e15e40-064a-11f1-b922-e51ff66e4291/file-6y3zli1mlg85w6e.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\"></p>\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; {[\\alpha]_{D \\text {-sucrose }}=+66.5^{\\circ}, \\quad[\\alpha]_{D \\text {-Glucose }}=+52.5^{\\circ}} \\\\ &amp; {[\\alpha]_{D \\text {-Fructose }}=-92.4^{\\circ}} \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n<p>⇒ Sucrose is dextrorotatory and hydrolysed product is laevorotatory.</p>",
      "marks": 4,
      "negativeMarks": -1,
      "topic": "Biomolecules"
    },
