      "questionText": "<p>The substituents R<sub>1</sub> and R<sub>2</sub> for nine peptides are listed in the table given below. How many of these peptides are positively charged at pH = 7.0 ?</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l24lqe58/73bb3039-1e97-48a4-bb66-d37ccee42c5a/2cfd75c0-bf06-11ec-8fbf-67f2639a0a45/file-1l24lqe59.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l24lqe58/73bb3039-1e97-48a4-bb66-d37ccee42c5a/2cfd75c0-bf06-11ec-8fbf-67f2639a0a45/file-1l24lqe59.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"IIT-JEE 2012 Paper 1 Offline Chemistry - Biomolecules Question 15 English\"></p>\n<p><style type=\"text/css\">\n.tg  {border-collapse:collapse;border-spacing:0;}\n.tg td{border-color:black;border-style:solid;border-width:1px;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;\n  overflow:hidden;padding:10px 5px;word-break:normal;}\n.tg th{border-color:black;border-style:solid;border-width:1px;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;\n  font-weight:normal;overflow:hidden;padding:10px 5px;word-break:normal;}\n.tg .tg-baqh{text-align:center;vertical-align:top}\n</style>\n</p><table class=\"tg\" style=\"undefined;table-layout: fixed; width: 848px\">\n<colgroup>\n<col style=\"width: 172px\">\n<col style=\"width: 312px\">\n<col style=\"width: 364px\">\n</colgroup>\n<thead>\n  <tr>\n    <th class=\"tg-baqh\">Peptide</th>\n    <th class=\"tg-baqh\">$${R_1}$$</th>\n    <th class=\"tg-baqh\">$${R_2}$$</th>\n  </tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n  <tr>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">I</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">H</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">H</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">II</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">H</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">$$C{H_3}$$<br></td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">III</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">$$C{H_2}COOH$$</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">H</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">IV</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">$$C{H_2}CON{H_2}$$</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">$${(C{H_2})_4}N{H_2}$$</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">V</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">$$C{H_2}CON{H_2}$$</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">$$C{H_2}CON{H_2}$$</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">VI</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">$${(C{H_2})_4}N{H_2}$$</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">$${(C{H_2})_4}N{H_2}$$</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">VII</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">$$C{H_2}COOH$$</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">$$C{H_2}CON{H_2}$$</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">VIII</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">$$C{H_2}OH$$</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">$${(C{H_2})_4}N{H_2}$$</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">IX</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">$${(C{H_2})_4}N{H_2}$$</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">$$C{H_3}$$</td>\n  </tr>\n</tbody>\n</table><p></p>",
      "options": [],
      "correctOption": 0,
      "solution": "<p>For basic amino acids with pH > 7, peptides will exist as cations. For example, when the substituents are basic, that is R<sub>1</sub> = CH<sub>2</sub>CONH<sub>2</sub> and R<sub>2</sub> = (CH<sub>2</sub>)<sub>4</sub>NH<sub>2</sub> or when R<sub>1</sub> = (CH<sub>2</sub>)<sub>4</sub>NH<sub>2</sub> and R<sub>2</sub> = (CH<sub>2</sub>)<sub>4</sub>NH<sub>2</sub> or when R<sub>1</sub> = CH<sub>2</sub>OH and R<sub>2</sub> = (CH<sub>2</sub>)<sub>4</sub>NH<sub>2</sub> or when R<sub>1</sub> = (CH<sub>2</sub>)<sub>4</sub>NH<sub>2</sub> and R<sub>2</sub> = CH<sub>3</sub>.</p>",
      "marks": 3,
      "negativeMarks": -1,
      "topic": "Biomolecules"
    }
  ]
